            <p><strong><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/06/technology/instagram-abuse-new-privacy.html" target="_blank">Instagram Introduces New Tools Meant to Curb Abuse and Expand Privacy</a></strong></p>
            <p>In December, Instagram announced that it would be offering more tools for its users to keep themselves protected from online abuse. These include the ability to remove others’ comments from their photo posts and to filter out certain followers. The increased ability to moderate comments also allows users to ‘like’ individual comments going forward. Additionally, users who keep their accounts private will be able to remove users they’ve previously approved, instead of needing to block the user as was required in the past. Instagram has also indicated that removed users will not be notified that they’ve been removed to reduce the prospect of online harassment.</p>
