            <p>The New York Times recounts 2016’s most popular tweets and hashtags, most of which were trending topics and shared tweets about news and politics. While it is likely no surprise that the United States presidential election garnered some of these top spots, other popular hashtags centered around identity and safety, such as #InternationalWomensDay and #BlackLivesMatter.</p>
