            <p><strong><a href="https://techcrunch.com/2016/12/15/twitter-cuts-dataminr-access-for-law-enforcement-fusion-centers/" target="_blank">Twitter Cuts Dataminr Access for Law Enforcement Fusion Centers</a></strong></p>
            <p>In a time where Americans are increasingly wary of government surveillance, particularly of their online activities, Twitter recently announced that it will be limiting the data access it provides to domestic surveillance hubs, including Dataminr, a social media monitoring firm Twitter partially owns. Dataminr has numerous government contracts—contracts that gave some concern to the ACLU about local and federal governments having unfettered access to Twitter’s data.</p>
