            <p><strong><a href="http://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2016/12/facebook-fake-news-germany-threatens-new-law-big-fines/" target="_blank">German Law Would Fine Social Media Sites “Publishing” Fake News</a></strong></p>
            <p>After the surprising results of the U.S. election in November, some critics focused on the role of fake news sites disseminating stories on Facebook and other social media sites. A proposed German law would impose fines on Facebook and similar social media sites for “publishing” fake news stories. This sudden interest in penalizing fake news sites could be in anticipation of the country’s elections coming up next year.</p>
