            <p><strong><a href="http://www.adweek.com/socialtimes/twitter-tweet-search-results-relevance/648648" target="_blank">Twitter Top Tweets Search Results Now Displayed by Relevance Instead of Chronologically</a></strong></p>
            <p>Departing from its traditional method of sorting search results by reverse chronology, Twitter now sorts search results by relevance. According to a statement by a senior software engineer, the company now uses an algorithm to rank relevant tweets within a time range. This change puts Twitter in line with general search engines, who have long sorted search results by relevance, using recency only as one factor in ranking.</p>
